<article>
  <div class="article-header">
    <h1>Fryeburg, ME Dispensary Guide</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Cannabis dispensaries in Fryeburg, Maine — Oxford County's premier destination</p>
  </div>

  <section class="fact-box">
    <h2>Fryeburg at a Glance</h2>
    <table aria-label="Fryeburg cannabis market overview">
      <thead><tr><th scope="col">Fact</th><th scope="col">Details</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Dispensaries in Town</strong></td><td>4+ (White Mountain Craft Cannabis, The Glass Cook, Above All Greenery, The Great Atlantic Puffin Company)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Opt-In Status</strong></td><td>YES — Recreational authorized</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Nearest Medical Dispensary</strong></td><td>Above All Greenery (299 Main St) and The Great Atlantic Puffin Company (235 Bridgton Rd)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Nearest Recreational</strong></td><td>White Mountain Craft Cannabis (285 Main St) — First rec dispensary in western Maine</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Population</strong></td><td>~3,500</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>County</strong></td><td>Oxford County</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>Fryeburg is one of Oxford County's most significant cannabis destinations. With four or more active dispensaries serving a town of only 3,500 residents, Fryeburg punches well above its weight class in the Maine cannabis market. The town's strategic position on the New Hampshire border, combined with its status as home to the first recreational dispensary in western Maine, makes it a regional hub that draws customers from across state lines.</p>
    <p>The Fryeburg Fair, held annually, draws more than 200,000 visitors to the region — creating a massive seasonal surge that benefits cannabis retailers who stock appropriately for tourist traffic. Pre-rolls, single-serve edibles, and portable products perform particularly well during fair season.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Dispensaries in Fryeburg</h2>

    <h3>White Mountain Craft Cannabis (Recreational)</h3>
    <p><strong>Address:</strong> 285 Main St Ste 8, Fryeburg, ME 04037</p>
    <p><strong>Phone:</strong> (207) 256-3082</p>
    <p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.whitemountaincraftcannabis.com">whitemountaincraftcannabis.com</a></p>
    <p><strong>Hours:</strong> Verify current hours on <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/White+Mountain+Craft+Cannabis+Fryeburg">Google Maps</a> or Apple Maps — they update seasonally. Yelp shows Mon-Sat 8am–6pm as of May 2026.</p>
    <p>White Mountain Craft Cannabis holds the distinction of being the first recreational cannabis dispensary in western Maine. Originally a medical dispensary, they became licensed for adult-use recreational sales in May 2025. Located on Main Street, they serve the adult-use market with a curated selection of cannabis products including their own lab-extracted tinctures and gummies. Their western Maine location makes them a convenient option for New Hampshire residents who can legally purchase in Maine but not in New Hampshire.</p>

    <h3>The Glass Cook (Medical + Glassblowing)</h3>
    <p><strong>Address:</strong> 295 Bridgton Rd, Fryeburg, ME 04037</p>
    <p><strong>Phone:</strong> (207) 890-8871</p>
    <p><strong>Hours:</strong> Mon–Sat 11am–7pm, Closed Sunday</p>
    <p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://theglasscook.com">theglasscook.com</a></p>
    <p>The Glass Cook is a unique destination combining a licensed caregiver/medical cannabis dispensary with an on-site glassblowing studio and Cured — their own cannabis kitchen specializing in edibles. They offer over 300 medical marijuana products across flower, pre-rolls, vapes, concentrates, drinks, tinctures, and small-batch edibles. Their storefront is also a headshop with CBD products and smoking accessories. Open Mon–Sat 11am–7pm, closed Sundays.</p>

    <h3>Above All Greenery North (Medical)</h3>
    <p><strong>Address:</strong> 48 Fair St Unit 4, Fryeburg, ME 04037</p>
    <p><strong>Phone:</strong> (207) 256-3340</p>
    <p><strong>Hours:</strong> Mon Closed, Tue–Fri 10am–6pm, Sat 10am–5pm, Sun 9am–5pm</p>
    <p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://aboveallgreenery.net">aboveallgreenery.net</a></p>
    <p>Above All Greenery North is the Fryeburg location of a Maine-based medical cannabis company with multiple dispensaries. All cannabis products are grown in-house, pesticide-free and tested by state-accredited labs. They serve medical cannabis patients from their new Fair Street location.</p>

    <h3>The Great Atlantic Puffin Company (Medical)</h3>
    <p><strong>Address:</strong> 235 Bridgton Rd, Fryeburg, ME 04037</p>
    <p><strong>Phone:</strong> (207) 935-5444</p>
    <p><strong>Hours:</strong> Mon–Sat 10am–6pm, Sun 10am–4pm</p>
    <p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://greatatlanticpuffinco.com">greatatlanticpuffinco.com</a></p>
    <p>The Great Atlantic Puffin Company operates a medical cannabis dispensary at 235 Bridgton Road. They also have a recreational location at 510 Portland Road in Bridgton. The Fryeburg location serves medical patients with cash and ATM on-site.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>NH Border Location — Cross-State Traffic</h2>
    <p>Fryeburg's position on the Maine-New Hampshire border creates a significant competitive advantage. New Hampshire has not legalized recreational cannabis for adult use, despite surrounding states doing so. This means New Hampshire residents who wish to purchase cannabis legally must either travel to Massachusetts or Maine. Fryeburg, being one of the closest Maine dispensaries to southern New Hampshire, captures substantial cross-state traffic.</p>
    <p>This border effect means that a dispensary in Fryeburg doesn't just compete for the local 3,500-person market — it serves an effective catchment area that extends deep into New Hampshire, potentially reaching customers from Conway, North Conway, Lincoln, and even Manchester (approximately 80 miles south).</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Town Status & Opt-In</h2>
    <p>Fryeburg has opted in to recreational cannabis, making it one of the few western Maine towns to do so. This progressive stance has paid dividends in tax revenue and economic development, with the cannabis industry providing jobs and foot traffic to local businesses.</p>
    <p>For current opt-in status and any municipal changes, refer to our <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-opt-in-tracker">Maine Cannabis Opt-In Tracker</a>.</p>
  </section>

